        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 2:34PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 234 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lagrange, or 18 miles southwest of Bolivar, moving southwest at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lamar, Lagrange, Michigan City, Slayden, Rossville, Moscow,
Williston, Grand Junction, La Grange, Saulsbury, Hudsonville, Early
Grove, Hays Crossing, Pattersonville, Forty Five, and Ghost River
State Natural Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
